  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You radiate a protective, unseeable aura in a 10-foot Emanation that originates from you. The aura is inactive while you have the &amp;Reference[Incapacitated apply=false] condition.</p><p>You and your allies in the aura gain a bonus to saving throws equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum bonus of +1, currently @abilities.cha.mod).</p><p>If another Paladin is present, a creature can benefit from only one Aura of Protection at a time; the creature chooses which aura while in them.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-psXxXY50igwsTfYC\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>Currently due to a bug in the dnd5e system, you will have to edit the effect that comes with this feature to reflect your CHA mod instead of using the formula as the formula will not work. Remember to update this if your CHA mod is ever changed.</p></section>",
